    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>ALMA capabilities are going to change our picture of the molecular components of
ISM in nearby galaxies, providing the unprecedented spatial resolution to
resolve molecular clouds in external galaxies, and the sensitivity to detect
molecular species so far too faint to be observed in non starburst environments.

We ask for observations in Band 3 of HCN(1-0) and HCO+(1-0) in two starforming
regions of the nearby star forming galaxy NGC3627, at a resolution of 2 arcsec.
These regions are located at two bar ends, corresponding to broad peaks of CO
and RC emissions. The requested data will complement already available
observations of CO and radio continuum emissions at the same resolution, and
archival optical and IR data, adding dense molecular tracers to the interstellar
medium multi-frequency study.</prp:abstract>
